<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[103671]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[A Bergman classic]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[The Argentinian director Daniel Veronese brings Autumn Sonata, one of the key works in Ingmar Bergman's filmography, to the Teatre Lliure.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Daniel Veronese stages one of the key works from Ingmar Bergman&#8217;s filmography at the Teatre Lliure: <i>Autumn Sonata</i>.</p>
<p>The play tells the story of Charlotte, a famous pianist who decides to spend some time in the house of her daughter, whom she hasn&#8217;t seen in seven years. Veronese once again deals with the deepest emotions involved in the relationship between a mother and daughter.</p>
